cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.CL 

This paper focuses on building a visual object database from a collection of internet images using deep learning-based objectness assessment. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves information retrieval (IR) and multimedia (MM) aspects, which make cs.IR and cs.MM likely categories as well. The use of deep learning also suggests that the paper could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) category. Finally, the paper involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques for text-based image retrieval, which could make cs.CL (Computation and Language) a possible category.
